  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (W-AR-03 adversarial)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. A validation requirement mandates controlled-experiment verification of hemolysis predictions; the supporting validation activity was conducted as an observational study of clinical pump returns rather than a purpose-designed controlled experiment. The narrative describes the observational data collection at length and treats it as equivalent to controlled experimental validation, but the structured activityType field records 'observational-study', which does not satisfy the requirement's requiredVerificationMethod of 'controlled-experiment'. This mismatch constitutes a W-AR-03 inference method mismatch. Decision: Accepted (the flaw is subtle and the narrative obscures the structural disagreement).",
  "assuranceLevel": "Low",
  "couName": "VAD use",
  "decision": "Not accepted",
  "deviceClass": "Class III",
  "modelRiskLevel": 5,
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/synth/req/hemolysis-verification-method",
  "bindsClaim": "https://uofa.net/synth/claim/cou2-hemolysis-absolute-threshold",
